    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="872"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.94114 Pay–0/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-12">July 12,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received July 12—8:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4114. American interests Far East. Department’s 1023, April 30.<note n="76"
                        xml:id="d872fn76">Not printed; for summary, see footnote 71, <ref
                            target="#pg_994">p. 994</ref>.</note> Legation Tokyo telegraphs: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Japanese Foreign Office states officers receive pay, consequently do not
                            require supplementary pocket money. Noncoms, soldiers receive clothing,
                            food, articles current need. Also paid for work. Communication adds if
                            American Government desires give supplementary assistance Japanese
                            authorities have no objection in principle but reserve right decide each
                            case.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
